      • onLoginButtonAction

        public void onLoginButtonAction​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                         throws java.io.IOException,
                                java.sql.SQLException
        Reaction to User clicking Login button, takes in String values from User facing username and password boxes and passes them to method validUser() to receive a boolean value of true and allow the login or of false to restrict the login and display an error message
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - User initiating button press
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - thrown in case of log file interaction issues
        java.sql.SQLException - thrown in case of SQL database interaction issues

      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        Initializer for login form screen, checks User's system information on timezone and language and adjusts displayed String values to reflect them. Loads String values from different ResourceBundles if the system default language is set to French, but otherwise defaults to English.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - resource location pointer
        resourceBundle - target ResourceBundle to select key values from
